Summary : This bar chart displays the daily electric usage in kilowatt hours (kWh) over a 13-month period, with each bar corresponding to a month and annotated with the average temperature for that month. bar chart: Title & Axes : • Title: "Electric Usage History - Kilowatt Hours (kWh)" • Y-axis: "kWh/Day" (range: 0 to 500, tick marks at 100, 200, 300, 400, 500) • X-axis: "Average Temperature" (months from May to May, each with average temperature in °F) Data Points : • May (62°): ~420 kWh/day • Jun (67°): ~440 kWh/day • Jul (75°): ~470 kWh/day • Aug (75°): ~460 kWh/day • Sep (64°): ~430 kWh/day • Oct (52°): ~400 kWh/day • Nov (45°): ~390 kWh/day • Dec (38°): ~430 kWh/day • Jan (34°): ~380 kWh/day • Feb (39°): ~410 kWh/day • Mar (39°): ~400 kWh/day • Apr (52°): ~400 kWh/day • May (56°): ~420 kWh/day (bar is green, others are gray) Design Encodings : • All bars are gray except the last (May 56°), which is green. • Bars are vertical, equally spaced, with month and average temperature labeled below each. • No gridlines or error bars. Distribution & Trends : • Usage peaks in July and August (~470 kWh/day). • Lowest usage in January (~380 kWh/day). • Usage is generally higher in summer months and lower in winter, with some fluctuation. Analysis : • Electric usage is highest during the warmest months (July, August) and lowest during the coldest month (January). • The most recent month (May 56°) is highlighted in green, possibly to indicate current or most relevant data. • There is a general pattern of increased usage during higher average temperatures, suggesting air conditioning or cooling as a major driver. • Usage does not drop as sharply in winter as it rises in summer, indicating some baseline or heating-related consumption. Supplier Information : • Supplier: DIRECT ENERGY BUSINESS, LLC. • Address: 1001 LIBERTY AVE, PITTSBURGH PA 15222-3714. • Phone: 888-925-9115.
